{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.33",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 33 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:1",
      "text": "Howbeit hear, Job, my words, and hearken to my speech.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:2",
      "text": "For behold, I have opened my mouth, and my tongue has spoken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:3",
      "text": "My heart shall be found pure by my words; and the understanding of my lips shall meditate purity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:4",
      "text": "The Divine Spirit is that which formed me, and the breath of the Almighty that which teaches me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:5",
      "text": "If thou canst, give me an answer: wait therefore; stand against me, and I will stand against thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:6",
      "text": "Thou art formed out of the clay as also I: we have been formed out of the same substance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:7",
      "text": "My fear shall not terrify thee, neither shall my hand be heavy upon thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:8",
      "text": "But thou hast said in mine ears, (I have heard the voice of thy words;) because thou sayest, I am pure, not having sinned;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:9",
      "text": "I am blameless, for I have not transgressed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:10",
      "text": "Yet he has discovered a charge against me, and he has reckoned me as an adversary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:11",
      "text": "And he has put my foot in the stocks, and has watched all my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:12",
      "text": "For how sayest thou, I am righteous, yet he has not hearkened to me? for he that is above mortals is eternal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:13",
      "text": "But thou sayest, Why has he not heard every word of my cause?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:14",
      "text": "For when the Lord speaks once, or a second time,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:15",
      "text": "sending a dream, or in the meditation of the night; (as when a dreadful alarm happens to fall upon men, in slumberings on the bed:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:16",
      "text": "then opens he the understanding of men: he scares them with such fearful visions:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:17",
      "text": "to turn a man from unrighteousness, and he delivers his body from a fall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:18",
      "text": "He spares also his soul from death, and suffers him not to fall in war.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:19",
      "text": "And again, he chastens him with sickness on his bed, and the multitude of his bones is benumbed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:20",
      "text": "And he shall not be able to take any food, though his soul shall desire meat;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:21",
      "text": "until his flesh shall be consumed, and he shall shew his bones bare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:22",
      "text": "His soul also draws nigh to death, and his life is in Hades.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:23",
      "text": "Though there should be a thousand messengers of death, not one of them shall wound him: if he should purpose in his heart to turn to the Lord, and declare to man his fault, and shew his folly;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:24",
      "text": "he will support him, that he should not perish, and will restore his body as fresh plaster upon a wall; and he will fill his bones with morrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:25",
      "text": "And he will make his flesh tender as that of a babe, and he will restore him among men in his full strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:26",
      "text": "And he shall pray to the Lord, and his prayer shall be accepted of him; he shall enter with a cheerful countenance, with a full expression of praise: for he will render to men their due.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:27",
      "text": "Even then a man shall blame himself, saying, What kind of things have I done? and he has not punished me according to the full amount of my sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:28",
      "text": "Deliver my soul, that it may not go to destruction, and my life shall see the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:29",
      "text": "Behold, all these things, the Mighty One works in a threefold manner with a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:30",
      "text": "And he has delivered my soul from death, that my life may praise him in the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:31",
      "text": "Hearken, Job, and hear me: be silent, and I will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:32",
      "text": "If thou hast words, answer me: speak, for I desire thee to be justified.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.33.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:33",
      "text": "If not, do thou hear me: be silent, and I will teach thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
